        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Hi people. \r\n\r\nIt will be very nice to be able to make forward to an existing email.\r\nThis will prevent lot of work and bugs like: what will happen if you have an html but set it text? what will happen if you have attachments or is multipart and other.\r\n\r\nI searched for this but didnt found anything so please forgive me if this request or feature exists already.\r\nIs first time I came here :).\r\n\r\nHow I see it now:\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n\/\/take an existing email\r\n$oldMail = new Zend_Mail_Storage_Imap();\r\n\r\n\/\/make new Zend_Mail that can accept a Zend_Mail_Storage_xx object\r\n$mail = new Zend_Mail($oldMail);\r\n\r\n\/\/set new to\r\n$mail->addTo($oneEmail);\r\n\r\n\/\/send\r\n$mail->send();\r\n{code}\r\n\r\ngreets,\r\nAlex\r\n"
        },
